To make the fishcakes, place all of the fishcake ingredients, except the oil, into a food processor and blend to a paste.Divide the mixture into two and shape the mixture into two patties.Heat the oil in a frying pan over a medium heat and gently fry the fishcakes for 4-5 minutes on each side, or until completely cooked through.For the vinaigrette, place all of the vinaigrette ingredients into a pan and cook until the red pepper is softened.To serve, place the fishcakes onto a warm plate and spoon the sauce around.